Lil Community by Lil Trails is an initiative to create a community of domain experts, parents and children who share and exchange ideas ranging across different topics. Presenting to you a wide array of speakers who’ll be conversing on Specially chosen topics that are relevant to the present scenario and much needed for all of us. 
Everyday 4 PM from 9 April to 13 April. 
We are so happy to have @lakshmiprashanth.dr @the_storytellingfellow @buncke @mythaunty @chordia.chirag on board and Thank them all for their time and support.

Janaki Aunty @maajanaki and Team Lil Trails @avantinatarajan @rajavel.sundar will be moderating the event with the guests. 
Don’t miss these wonderful sessions

Online Story Fest 2.0 is here. 
@liltrails and Golpo Tales will be organising the Second Edition of Online Story Fest between 6th April and 10th April at 5:00 PM. 
@maajanaki Aunty will be narrating a story everyday for 15 Minutes followed by a Craft activity by @liltrails that is based on the story. The children can create the craft along with guided instructions from @liltrails. 
The event will take place over Zoom Meetings and all will have face-to-face interaction with Janaki Aunty and Team Lil Trails. 
The Fee is ₹300 per Day per Child. 
A 5 Day pass can be obtained at a special price of ₹1250 .

Register on https://liltrails.com/

Registrations close on April 4 and limited spots are available. 
#storytelling #indianstories #craft #chennaimothers #storiesandcraft #liltrails #janakisabesh #golpotales #storiesforall #momsandcrafts #indianstorytellers #janakisabesh #storyteller #everyonehasastory
